WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:03.878
♪♪

00:28.319 --> 00:32.115
I told my sister to tell her
these little rich kids she's
running around smoking pot with,

00:32.115 --> 00:35.660
they get through this
hippie phase, their parents
are gonna set them up with jobs.

00:35.660 --> 00:38.705
Your niece is a bright girl.
She'll be all right.

00:38.705 --> 00:41.374
I said, "It won't be
like that for you."
(siren wailing)

00:41.374 --> 00:44.002
-Oh, shoot.
-OFFICER ON LOUDSPEAKER:
Pull over.

00:44.002 --> 00:46.921
-I told you
about that taillight.
-Yeah.

00:54.679 --> 00:57.807
Driver,
step out of the car
with your hands up.

01:02.228 --> 01:04.147
Listen, I'm on the job.

01:04.147 --> 01:07.192
Get your hands up
on top of that car.

01:07.192 --> 01:10.653
Passenger side,
same thing, out of the car.
Put your hands up on top.

01:10.653 --> 01:14.365
-Look, I said I'm on the job.
-Passenger side,
get out of that car now.

01:14.365 --> 01:16.659
Put your hands up on top.

01:18.953 --> 01:22.957
I'm a New York City
police lieutenant.
My shield's in my pocket.

01:22.957 --> 01:26.211
All right, let me see it.
Take it out, slow.

01:33.593 --> 01:36.638
Sorry about that.
Can't blame me
for being careful.

01:36.638 --> 01:39.099
You know you got a taillight
burnt out back here?

01:39.099 --> 01:41.434
-You all right?
-Yeah.

01:41.434 --> 01:44.395
You stopped us like
you had my description
on a bank robbery.

01:44.395 --> 01:47.816
All due respect,
you're gonna tell me
how to do a car stop now?

01:47.816 --> 01:50.735
-Officer, you get a good look
at this shield?
-Yeah, I did, Lieutenant.

01:50.735 --> 01:54.989
And I'm saying
V.T.L., Section 375.2,

01:54.989 --> 01:57.408
a taillight out
is a "summonsable" offense.

01:57.408 --> 01:59.619
Do me a favor, you wanna
to give me a summons,
give it to me,

01:59.619 --> 02:02.539
but don't lecture me
on vehicle and traffic law.

02:02.539 --> 02:05.834
I'm doing my job, sir.

02:05.834 --> 02:10.421
How about you just
get this taillight
taken care of?

02:10.421 --> 02:13.216
-Arthur, let's go.
-(police radio chatter)

02:19.430 --> 02:24.227
-How do you say that name?
-Sha-manski.
You wanna write it down?

02:24.227 --> 02:26.062
-What's your name?
-John McCaslin.

02:26.062 --> 02:28.398
You sure you don't wanna
give me a summons?

02:30.024 --> 02:33.653
The two of you
have a nice night.

02:33.653 --> 02:34.737
Let's get out of here.

02:37.824 --> 02:39.826
(engine starts)

02:39.826 --> 02:43.580
(tires squealing)

02:44.205 --> 02:47.208
♪♪

03:50.688 --> 03:52.649
(chattering)

03:59.239 --> 04:01.032
(sighs)

04:17.632 --> 04:20.176
(sighs)

04:36.150 --> 04:39.779
Could I switch seats with you?
It'd be a big favor.

04:39.779 --> 04:42.407
-Yeah.
-Appreciate it.

04:56.629 --> 04:58.881
-Son?
-Hey, Pop.

04:58.881 --> 05:02.802
Aw, Andy.
Can I give you a kiss?

05:02.802 --> 05:06.014
-Will they throw us out?
-Oh, my God.

05:06.014 --> 05:07.849
I can't believe it's you.

05:07.849 --> 05:10.310
(both laughing)

05:11.811 --> 05:13.646
How you been?
How's Theo?

05:13.646 --> 05:15.815
Oh, God,
he's--he's wonderful.

05:15.815 --> 05:19.193
He had some health questions,
but he-he's fine.

05:19.193 --> 05:23.197
-And Sylvia's good?
-She's wonderful.
She's a wonderful mother.

05:24.866 --> 05:27.410
You know,
I'm trying to understand
what's going on.

05:27.410 --> 05:30.997
You know, I'm--I'm dead,
but I'm--I'm doing all right.

05:33.249 --> 05:36.586
I, uh--I wish
we'd have seen you sooner.

05:38.212 --> 05:41.632
We had a lot of sorrow
with your death.

05:42.842 --> 05:45.553
Pop, we didn't see each other
too much when I was alive.

05:46.679 --> 05:48.723
What's your inference
with that?

05:48.723 --> 05:51.225
No, I'm just saying,
you know?

05:51.225 --> 05:53.227
Nobody says I didn't make
any mistakes.

05:53.227 --> 05:55.646
I would've liked
to have seen the baby
and Sylvia too.

05:55.646 --> 05:59.567
-That's all I'm saying.
-I took you
for breaking balls,

05:59.567 --> 06:01.527
my not seeing you
growing up.

06:03.446 --> 06:05.490
It's a little late
about that, Pop.

06:09.911 --> 06:13.664
I wish to hell
they'd let you
come over there, Andy.

06:13.664 --> 06:17.168
The little guy, huh,
well, he's a real pisser.

06:17.168 --> 06:20.046
And in 40 ways
he reminds me of you.

06:20.046 --> 06:24.342
I never say that to Sylvia
'cause of the upset.

06:26.427 --> 06:29.222
Did I just ruin something now
with my nature?

06:29.222 --> 06:35.103
No. Anyways,
um, I gotta go.

06:35.103 --> 06:37.688
If I offended anybody,
let 'em know
I try to curb it.

06:37.688 --> 06:41.067
Yeah, I-I don't know
how it works.

06:41.067 --> 06:43.903
I love you, Pop.

06:43.903 --> 06:46.697
Any opportunity,
any modification on my part--

06:46.697 --> 06:48.574
Love to Sylvia
and the baby.

06:50.701 --> 06:53.454
Take good care of yourself
as you can.

07:06.717 --> 07:07.885
My son.

07:07.885 --> 07:10.930
He's a good-looking boy.

07:10.930 --> 07:14.642
I did something here.
They pulled him.

07:16.352 --> 07:19.522
Is that it for him,
or is he coming back?

07:19.522 --> 07:24.068
-I can't talk no more.
-Should've talked across me.

07:24.068 --> 07:26.529
I can't talk no more.
I'm finished.

07:29.574 --> 07:32.743
(phone ringing)

07:33.494 --> 07:36.372
(ringing continues)

07:38.416 --> 07:41.210
Sipowicz.

07:41.210 --> 07:43.838
(sighs)
Where?

07:45.047 --> 07:47.383
(clears throat)
All right.

07:58.603 --> 08:01.189
What is it, Andy?

08:01.189 --> 08:05.234
Another bar stickup.
Civilian shot.

08:05.234 --> 08:07.069
They're bringing him
to the squad room
from the hospital.

08:07.069 --> 08:12.575
-You were talking
in your sleep.
-What did I say?

08:12.575 --> 08:14.494
I wasn't listening very well.

08:17.788 --> 08:19.790
I gotta go
talk to this guy.

08:33.846 --> 08:36.807
Appreciate you being able
to help, Mr. Galasso.

08:36.807 --> 08:40.394
Uh, coming in and all
being injured. Have a seat.
This is Detective Sipowicz.

08:40.394 --> 08:42.772
-Hi.
-I want you to find out
who these guys are...

08:42.772 --> 08:45.233
-and what they--what they
were trying to prove.
-Yeah.

08:45.233 --> 08:46.817
What time did they come
into the bar, sir?

08:46.817 --> 08:49.403
Ah, they come in about
a quarter after 1:00.

08:49.403 --> 08:53.241
One orders a Jack Daniel's,
the other one a gin and tonic.

08:53.241 --> 08:55.409
Had they been
in there before?

08:55.409 --> 08:59.580
Well, if they cased the place,
I never seen 'em. I don't know
what kind of crooks--

08:59.580 --> 09:03.834
Jack Daniel's, he pulls out
this piece of crap,
looks like a .22.

09:03.834 --> 09:07.255
Night guy said,
they got a .25 shell casing
off the floor.

09:07.255 --> 09:09.840
Okay, same difference.
It was a puny gun.

09:09.840 --> 09:13.052
I'm thinking it's a joke.
The other guy,
he don't have dick.

09:13.052 --> 09:15.054
They go,
"It's a robbery."

09:15.054 --> 09:17.765
"A robbery?
Who the hell do you--

09:17.765 --> 09:20.851
Get outta here before
I beat your skulls in!"

09:20.851 --> 09:24.063
And then jerk-off
shoots me in the head.

09:24.063 --> 09:26.857
Only what happens,
the bullet don't penetrate.

09:26.857 --> 09:30.069
So, I'm pouring blood,
I jump over the bar,

09:30.069 --> 09:33.072
"You yellow rat bastards,
I'll kill ya."

09:33.072 --> 09:35.449
I'm chasing 'em around
until they, uh,
run out the back way.

09:35.449 --> 09:38.953
-You can give us descriptions?
-Ah, the faggot
sons of bitches!

09:38.953 --> 09:41.789
I'd like to rip
their hearts out!

09:41.789 --> 09:44.166
(sighs)

09:44.166 --> 09:46.460
Ah, let me remember.

09:46.460 --> 09:50.506
It was, uh, two, uh,
nondescript-looking,

09:50.506 --> 09:53.884
skinny white kids,
in their 20s.

09:53.884 --> 09:57.263
One's got short hair,
a baseball cap.

09:57.263 --> 10:00.683
Nothing special.
No, uh, mustaches or nothing.

10:00.683 --> 10:02.935
What about what
they were dressed like?

10:02.935 --> 10:06.105
Like I was checkin' 'em out.
The hell do I know
what they had on?

10:06.105 --> 10:08.107
-All right.
-Regular clothes.

10:08.107 --> 10:10.109
The douche bag with the gun,

10:10.109 --> 10:13.112
if I ran into him
in the subway,
I bet I could spot him.

10:13.112 --> 10:16.532
We should get you
with a sketch artist.
You mind coming back in?

10:16.532 --> 10:20.328
Well, I'd like to
try and get some sleep,
if I could.

10:20.328 --> 10:22.496
Although, I-I'm
so worked up about this.

10:22.496 --> 10:26.167
How about we call you at noon,
Mr. Galasso? Have you
come back for a sketch.

10:26.167 --> 10:29.128
-Yeah, yeah, all right, then.
-We really appreciate it.

10:36.427 --> 10:38.554
Did you have any brothers
disappear at birth?

10:39.680 --> 10:41.557
What do you mean?

10:44.143 --> 10:47.146
Bobby, uh--(clears throat)
I'd like to catch
a nap myself...

10:47.146 --> 10:49.148
-before day tour gets in.
-You going upstairs?

10:49.148 --> 10:51.734
Yeah.
Get on this thing fresh.

10:51.734 --> 10:53.736
I'm sick of these guys
making us look like jerks.

10:53.736 --> 10:55.946
And they're willing
to use that gun now.

10:55.946 --> 10:58.949
Lucky for this guy
it was just a .25, huh?

10:58.949 --> 11:01.452
You think anything would have
penetrated that head?

11:02.953 --> 11:05.581
Let me see
if I can nap upstairs.

11:10.961 --> 11:14.256
♪♪

11:23.182 --> 11:25.101
(sighs)

11:37.279 --> 11:39.323
Son of a bitch.

11:44.620 --> 11:47.998
Excuse me. I'm looking for
either Detective Simone
or Sipowicz.

11:47.998 --> 11:49.917
Ah, that's
Detective Simone.

11:49.917 --> 11:52.253
Thanks. Detective.

11:52.253 --> 11:56.132
Hi. I'm Eddie Hazel,
Midtown South.
How you doing?

11:56.132 --> 11:58.467
Bobby Simone.
Are you working
on a bar robbery...

11:58.467 --> 12:01.971
-from earlier this
morning down on Mott Street?
-You know something about that?

12:01.971 --> 12:05.099
10:00 last night, sports bar
on East 38th Street's held up.

12:05.099 --> 12:08.185
Could be the same perps.
So, you wanna
compare notes?

12:08.185 --> 12:10.896
-Yeah, sure. Let's go
into the coffee room.
-Okay.

12:10.896 --> 12:12.898
-Tell me your name again.
-Eddie Hazel.

12:12.898 --> 12:14.900
-Call me Eddie.
-You new
over there, Eddie?

12:14.900 --> 12:16.902
Six weeks.
Just came over
from Transit.

12:16.902 --> 12:19.071
-Yeah. So how you like it
above ground?
-Love it.

12:19.071 --> 12:21.615
-Hey, Gina.
-Hey, James.

12:21.615 --> 12:25.911
James, see that woman
in a wheelchair
in the vending area downstairs?

12:25.911 --> 12:29.457
-I saw her with another woman.
-The woman was apparently
the victim of a con game.

12:29.457 --> 12:31.959
-She's out $5,000.
-Wheelchair bound?

12:31.959 --> 12:35.254
These scam artists, they're
always targeting the weaker.
That's the lowest of the low.

12:35.254 --> 12:39.091
Let me get squared away
in the locker room, and then
I'll go down and see her.

12:39.091 --> 12:41.051
-I'll talk to you later, Gina.
-Bye, James.

12:41.051 --> 12:45.264
Gina, there'll be two officers
from the 111th by here
some time this morning.

12:45.264 --> 12:47.558
If I'm not in my office,
have them go in there and wait.

12:47.558 --> 12:49.477
Sure, Lieutenant.

12:51.979 --> 12:54.857
Good-sized crowd
is watching the Knicks.

12:54.857 --> 12:58.068
These two come in
and order a gin and tonic
and a Jack Daniel's.

12:58.068 --> 13:01.447
That's their thing.
Comes to find out, the bar's
got a betting pool going.

13:01.447 --> 13:04.658
-Mm-hmm.
-Bartender aims to pay off
after the game's over.

13:04.658 --> 13:10.498
These two perps whip out
their little poop-butt pistol
and walk away with $1,500.

13:10.498 --> 13:12.541
So, when you heard what went
down over on Mott Street--

13:12.541 --> 13:15.211
I wonder if these jokers figured
it was their lucky night.

13:15.211 --> 13:17.505
Yeah, they're lucky.
They're lucky
this dude they shot...

13:17.505 --> 13:20.424
didn't beat 'em to death
with a barstool.

13:20.424 --> 13:22.760
I'd like to
talk to that fellow.
Well, if it's cool with you.

13:22.760 --> 13:25.179
Yeah. Here you go.

13:25.179 --> 13:28.307
This guy, Galasso, he's got
a bit of an attitude,
but he wants to cooperate.

13:28.307 --> 13:33.145
Okay. Bartender at Hondo's
named Bill McGregor.
Here's his home phone number.

13:33.145 --> 13:37.525
You might have to push him
a bit. Behind the betting,
he was a little shy to open up.

13:37.525 --> 13:40.903
-All right.
-Hey, uh,
tell me something.

13:40.903 --> 13:43.072
What happened to your P.A.A.?
Well, if I can ask.

13:43.072 --> 13:46.700
-Attempted rape.
Scumbag cut her up.
-Damn.

13:46.700 --> 13:49.703
-Was he caught?
-Mm-hmm.
Our squad got him.

13:49.703 --> 13:53.582
Way to go.
You know what?
She's still a pretty girl.

13:53.582 --> 13:56.043
All right, uh, Bobby.

13:56.043 --> 13:59.505
Thanks for the coffee,
and, uh, you take it easy, man.

13:59.505 --> 14:01.799
You too, Eddie.

14:01.799 --> 14:03.843
Let's one of us
catch these jokers, man.

14:07.429 --> 14:10.808
And the white woman
took out a cellular phone
and called her boss,

14:10.808 --> 14:13.727
supposedly a lawyer,
and asked what we should do.

14:13.727 --> 14:16.480
He said bring the money
down to his office
and he would check on...

14:16.480 --> 14:19.149
if it was counterfeit,
and then we'd be able
to split it.

14:19.149 --> 14:22.152
You, the white woman
and the black girl
were gonna split it?

14:22.152 --> 14:24.738
I mean,
I did talk to this man
on the phone myself.

14:24.738 --> 14:28.242
-He did sound like a lawyer.
-He sounded like a lawyer?

14:28.242 --> 14:31.161
Oh, God, Sis,
you're not that dumb.

14:31.161 --> 14:34.373
Mrs. Duffy,
what did he say to you,
the man on the phone?

14:34.373 --> 14:36.959
He said for us
to share the $60,000,

14:36.959 --> 14:40.170
we should each put up
some money of our own
to show good faith...

14:40.170 --> 14:43.173
-while he checked on
if the other was counterfeit.
-You weren't suspicious?

14:43.173 --> 14:45.968
This had to be cash?
What does that even mean,
"show good faith"?

14:45.968 --> 14:48.762
I can't explain.
That wasn't money
you could afford to lose.

14:48.762 --> 14:51.557
These people are experts
at manipulating
people's trust.

14:51.557 --> 14:54.768
They've probably
run the same scam
a hundred times.

14:54.768 --> 14:58.355
Don't feel ashamed
you were victimized.
What happened next, ma'am?

14:58.355 --> 15:02.902
The woman took
$5,000 from her bank,
or so I thought.

15:02.902 --> 15:05.195
And then I withdrew mine.

15:05.195 --> 15:08.157
Her taking her money out
first, that was part of
gaining your confidence.

15:08.157 --> 15:11.785
And then the black girl
said she needed
a ride to her bank,

15:11.785 --> 15:15.623
but with my wheelchair,
I should wait
at this coffee shop.

15:15.623 --> 15:21.420
I was given this zippered bag
to hold onto in the meantime
with the $60,000.

15:21.420 --> 15:23.422
Which was really
chopped up newspaper.

15:23.422 --> 15:28.761
Oh, as soon as I got in the car,
I knew I'd made a terrible,
terrible mistake.

15:28.761 --> 15:31.972
I'm gonna do my best
to catch the people
who did this to you.

15:31.972 --> 15:35.517
(sighs)
What are we supposed
to do now, Sis, huh?

15:35.517 --> 15:38.228
How can I have peace of mind,
you living independent
by yourself,

15:38.228 --> 15:40.147
if you let this happen?

15:42.983 --> 15:46.445
Hey, Lombardi.
What's doing?
Yeah, I'm good.

15:46.445 --> 15:51.283
Listen, uh, Eddie Hazel,
he came by the house
this morning. Uh--

15:51.283 --> 15:53.619
He's working
on some bar stickups?

15:53.619 --> 15:57.331
Yeah, he gave me
a phone number on a witness
from Hondo's Bar.

15:57.331 --> 16:00.042
And, uh,
I don't know, man.

16:00.042 --> 16:04.046
I must have wrote down
the number wrong here,
because--What?

16:04.046 --> 16:06.465
Really?

16:06.465 --> 16:11.512
Ah, oh, could you
do me a favor then,
and check the 61?

16:11.512 --> 16:13.889
Yeah, the guy's name
is McGregor. Psst.

16:13.889 --> 16:16.517
-Thanks.
-What's going on?

16:16.517 --> 16:20.479
Some detective from Midtown
South came over this morning,
looking to swap information.

16:20.479 --> 16:23.357
So, there's a mix-up
on this phone number of
a witness that he gave me.

16:23.357 --> 16:26.402
Lombardi's saying,
"I'm surprised this jerk would
even give a phone number to"--

16:26.402 --> 16:29.196
Hello. Yeah.

16:29.196 --> 16:33.534
Mm-hmm. 2739.

16:33.534 --> 16:36.078
Right.
What about the home address?
Is that on there?

16:37.413 --> 16:39.248
Uh-huh.

16:39.248 --> 16:43.711
So, what you were saying
before about this guy Hazel,
what's the deal with him?

16:43.711 --> 16:47.172
Yeah, huh?
(whispers)
Asshole.

16:47.172 --> 16:50.509
Yeah.
All right. Thanks.
Thanks for saying it.

16:50.509 --> 16:54.513
-Yeah, take care.
-What'd he say?

16:54.513 --> 16:57.307
This Eddie Hazel,
he's pissed off half the squad
over there already.

16:57.307 --> 16:59.643
He's an ex-Transit cop
looking to set the world
on fire.

16:59.643 --> 17:02.021
He's stealing collars
from his own guys.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.897
Think him giving you
the wrong number's
on purpose?

17:03.897 --> 17:07.526
Lombardi said that.
Said that's the kind
of silly crap that he's doing.

17:07.526 --> 17:09.611
-You got the legit number
and address there?
-Yeah.

17:09.611 --> 17:12.906
Bartender at a place
got hit a few hours before
this Mott Street tavern.

17:12.906 --> 17:17.661
Let's check him out.
Surprise this asshole detective
we found the guy.

17:17.661 --> 17:20.664
♪♪

17:29.673 --> 17:33.135
Lieutenant?
Sergeant calls us at home,
says we're to come talk to you.

17:33.135 --> 17:37.931
Yeah, good morning.
I wanted to talk to you
about the incident last night.

17:37.931 --> 17:40.142
The incident?

17:40.142 --> 17:43.562
I'm curious what was
going through your mind,

17:43.562 --> 17:47.149
deciding a busted taillight
warranted me and my wife...

17:47.149 --> 17:49.943
being treated like,
uh, Bonnie and Clyde.

17:49.943 --> 17:53.947
Lieutenant, I regret
whatever the inconvenience
to your wife or yourself,

17:53.947 --> 17:55.783
but we got to protect
ourselves out there.

17:55.783 --> 17:57.951
You wouldn't be here
if I thought it was
about protecting yourself.

17:57.951 --> 18:01.789
I can't help what you think.
Until I have control
of a situation out there,

18:01.789 --> 18:03.665
how am I supposed to know
what I'm dealing with?

18:04.458 --> 18:06.585
Do you feel the situation
was handled appropriately?

18:06.585 --> 18:09.588
It's me who pulled
you over, sir. It's me
you got the beef with.

18:09.588 --> 18:12.382
Officer McCaslin
can't speak for himself?

18:12.382 --> 18:13.967
How about it?

18:13.967 --> 18:18.180
Well, police have gotten shot
during car stops. We need to
protect ourselves.

18:18.180 --> 18:20.974
-How long you been
on the street?
-Ten months.

18:20.974 --> 18:23.185
-You?
-Six and a half years.

18:23.185 --> 18:25.604
-Queens the whole time?
-So what?

18:25.604 --> 18:28.398
So what did you perceive
as so threatening
about me...

18:28.398 --> 18:31.068
that you reacted
